<figureCitation box="[601,712,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,1344,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1338,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Berlandina avishur n. sp. ♂, holotype, left palpus. 1. Mesal view. 2. Ventral view. 3. Retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186953/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
); thick, round apical part of conductor bears on top a small transparent, pointed process (
<figureCitation box="[494,598,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[157,1424,1344,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1338,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Berlandina avishur n. sp. ♂, holotype, left palpus. 1. Mesal view. 2. Ventral view. 3. Retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186953/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
